trend_summary: Across the series the landscape stays dominantly forest-and-field. Forest edges are gradually cut back and central cropland blocks widen, while only small clusters of farmsteads enlarge. A few new straight roads appear but no sizeable urban core forms. Overall character remains rural with sparse, dispersed buildings.
notable_changes: Cropland blocks in the central corridor widen and merge, replacing forest patches.
Forest loss along northern and eastern edges, visible as new clearings.
Minor infill around scattered farmsteads; building footprints grow slightly.
New straight access road constructed linking southern clearings to the east.
Localized regrowth/reforestation on western hills balances some earlier clearing.
